cancelAllPending().details: Sets the executed flag to true for all pending calls

constructor.details: Initializes the contract, setting the owner and laminator addresses.

params._callBreaker: The address of the call breaker contract.
params._laminator: The address of the laminator contract.
params._owner: The address of the contract's owner.

copyCurrentJob(uint256,bytes).custom:reverts: It reverts if the sequence number is not set or if the sender is not the proxy.
copyCurrentJob(uint256,bytes).details: This function can only be called by the LaminatedProxy contract itself.

params.delay: The number of blocks to delay before the copied job can be executed.
params.shouldCopy: The condition under which the job should be copied.

returns._0: The sequence number of the copied job.

count().details: This is an alias for nextSequenceNumber(). It allows clearer code when      reading from the contract.

returns._count: The sequence number of the next call pushed to the laminated mempool.

execute(bytes).details: Decodes the provided `input` into a CallObject and then calls `_execute`.      Can only be invoked by the owner of the contract.

params.input: The encoded CallObject containing information about the function call to execute.

returns._0: returnValue The return value from the executed function call.

returns._execCallIndex: The sequence number of the currently executing call.

returns._execSeqNum: The sequence number of the currently executing call.

returns._isExec: Whether or not a call is executing in the laminator

pull(uint256).details: Executes the deferred call specified by the sequence number `seqNumber`.      This function performs a series of checks before calling `_execute` to      execute the deferred call. It emits a `CallPulled` event and deletes      the deferred call object from the `deferredCalls` mapping.

params.seqNumber: The sequence number of the deferred call to be executed.

returns.returnValue: The return value of the executed deferred call.

push(bytes,uint256).details: Adds a new CallObject to the `deferredCalls` mapping and emits a CallPushed event.      The function can only be called by the Laminator or the LaminatedProxy contract itself.      It can also be called re-entrantly to enable the contract to do cronjobs with tail recursion.

params.delay: The number of blocks to delay before the function call can be executed.      Use 0 for no delay.
params.input: The encoded CallObject containing information about the function call to defer.

returns.callSequenceNumber: The sequence number assigned to this deferred call.

viewDeferredCall(uint256).details: Returns a tuple containing a boolean indicating whether the deferred call exists,      and the CallObject containing details of the deferred function call.

params.seqNumber: The sequence number of the deferred function call to view.

returns._0: exists A boolean indicating whether the deferred call exists.
returns._1: callObj The CallObject containing details of the deferred function call.
